.\bugs.md:175:- **Current status:** Remediated locally on `sandbox-albert`. `Customer.selectedVendor` now maps the payload and updates the matching `RFQItem` row, using `rfqItem_id` first and `rfqItem_style_number` as the fallback.
.\bugs.md:180:### BACKEND-H6 — `findRFQAddProductLayout` references an undefined variable
.\bugs.md:283:- **What it is:** In `checkRFQStyleNumber` and `checkItemHeaderItemNumber`, if a matching record exists, `priceCodeIsChecked` never becomes `true` and the `while` loop re-runs the same `findOne` query indefinitely.
.\bugs.md:285:- **Current status:** Remediated locally on `sandbox-albert`. Item-number generation now checks each candidate once against `itemHeader.item_num_id` and `RFQItem.rfqItem_style_number`, retries at most 25 times, and returns a 409-style response if every candidate collides.
.\bugs.md:397:- **What it is:** `logging: console.log` is set on the main RFQ grid query, `grid.service`, `std.service`, `getMerchGroup`, `getViewlayout`, `getAuditLog`, and several others.
.\bugs.md:483:### DATA-SYNCING-M2 — `productions.js` model is actually `RFQItemStatus` — no productions model exists
.\bugs.md:487:- **What it is:** `productions.js` calls `sequelize.define('RFQItemStatus', ...)` on `RFQItemStatus` table. `sequelize.define` now runs twice for the same model name. There is no actual productions model.
.\bugs.md:488:- **What it causes:** The `RFQItemStatus` model is registered twice (second silently wins). Any code expecting a `productions` model reference would fail.
