designflow-backend\AGENTS.md:422:**Actually:** `quote_id` (`RFQVendor_id`) is a sequential integer, so a malicious vendor could enumerate other factories' quotes and POST `updateVendor` / `keepPrice` against them (IDOR). The guard blocks the one real case — a `vendor` whose token `factory_id` differs from the quote's `vendor_id_fk` — and deliberately **fails open** for internal roles, vendors with no `factory_id` on their token (legacy records), and quote rows with no `vendor_id_fk`. The intent is to close the enumeration hole without ever locking out a legitimate user (notably the invite-an-individual-vendor-to-one-item flow, where the invited factory owns its own quote row).
designflow-backend\AGENTS.md:492:**Recovery:** Quoted the identifier (commit `a556d3f` → `ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS "rfqItem_price_sales_snapshots" TEXT`) and added `ALTER TABLE "RFQItem" DROP COLUMN IF EXISTS "rfqitem_price_sales_snapshots"` (commit `476e453`) to remove the empty lowercase orphan column. Corrected `tests/unit/db.migration.test.js` to require the quoted form and added guards: fail on the unquoted form, assert the orphan DROP exists, assert the correct mixed-case column is never dropped.
