designflow-backend\docs\architecture.md:136:- Vendor quotes (in `routes/lib.router.js`): `POST /updateVendor`, `/sendPriceReq`, `/addingVendor`. **Re-quote (stale price refresh):** `POST /requestRequote` (internal roles only — flags a factory's quote and emails the factory for a fresh price) and `POST /keepPrice` (vendor reconfirms the current price, clearing the flag). Both resolve the quote by `quote_id` (`RFQVendor_id`) and run through the `vendorMayModifyQuote` ownership guard. See `models/lib.model.js` `Customer.requestRequote` / `Customer.keepPrice`.
designflow-backend\docs\architecture.md:137:- **Archive:** `POST /archiveRFQItem` archives/un-archives an item. For internal roles it toggles the global `RFQItem.rfqItem_archive`; for vendors it toggles a **per-vendor** `RFQVendor_archived` on their own quote row (so it never hides the item from Sourcing or other factories). On a vendor's list load, `Customer.getAll` auto-archives that factory's priced quotes older than 3 months (`helpers/archive-stale-quotes.js`). A vendor un-archive is sticky (`RFQVendor_archive_optout`); `requestRequote`, a fresh price, and `keepPrice` auto-un-archive / reset the cycle. See AGENTS.md §11.
designflow-backend\docs\architecture.md:280:**`RFQVendor.requote_requested`** (`BOOLEAN DEFAULT false`, added 2026-06): true when Sourcing has asked a factory to refresh a stale quote. Set by `requestRequote`; cleared by `keepPrice`, by a new vendor price in `updateVendorData`. Surfaced to the frontend in `helpers/utility.js` `remapRFQItem` (drives the orange price cell + bilingual "Quoted &lt;date&gt;" tooltip in the RFQ detail grid). The migration quotes the identifier (`"requote_requested"`) per the SYS-002 rule even though it is all-lowercase.
designflow-backend\docs\architecture.md:282:**`RFQVendor.RFQVendor_archived`** (`BOOLEAN DEFAULT false`, added 2026-06): per-vendor archive flag on a factory's own quote row. Drives the vendor's archive/active tab split in `Customer.getAll` (vendors filter `$RFQVendors.RFQVendor_archived$`; internal roles still use the global `RFQItem.rfqItem_archive`). Auto-set by the lazy sweep `helpers/archive-stale-quotes.js` `archiveStaleVendorQuotes()` for priced quotes whose `quote_date` is &gt;3 months old. Mixed-case identifier — migration quotes it (`"RFQVendor_archived"`).
designflow-backend\docs\architecture.md:284:**`RFQVendor.RFQVendor_archive_optout`** (`BOOLEAN DEFAULT false`, added 2026-06): sticky "vendor manually un-archived this" marker. The sweep skips rows where this (or `requote_requested`) `IS NOT true`, so a manual un-archive isn't undone on the next list load. Cleared on `requestRequote`, a fresh vendor price (`updateVendor`), and `keepPrice`, so the 3-month auto-archive cycle restarts. See AGENTS.md §11 for the full lifecycle.
